The problem is, unless valid recall petitions are filed on many of them ASAP, there aren't many of these dysfunctional place holders up for re-election this Nov.    
We really can't wait through several more legislative sessions, accumulating an ever greater burden of trivial, largely unconstitutional legislation and debilitating cuts in gov't services - BUT we're stuck - either we go for several more sessions w/o ever addressing the real problems, or we put up with what this lot finally patches together, no matter how bad it is.
{People, PLEASE, be Much more careful what/who you vote for in the future, checking past performances and connections Very carefully.  And lets quit this ridiculous habit of just lazily voting incumbents back in because they did favors w/in your district!  We need people to govern the State as a whole}
